  user_input {
    user_response: "Build a web application for an AI-powered proactive productivity companion called \"Last-Minute Life Saver.\"\n\nThe application must feature a split-screen dashboard layout optimized for desktop viewports. The left side must feature an intentional, low-friction conversational chat interface where users can type unstructured, frantic \"brain dumps\" of their schedules, tasks, or upcoming deadlines. The right side must feature a dynamic, interactive visual timeline and task execution board that updates in real-time based on the AI\'s analysis.\n\nKey components to generate in the React frontend:\n\nA clean Chat UI with state management to pass unstructured user inputs to a backend service.\n\nA Task Triage Matrix that visually categorizes tasks into structural states: Urgent & Critical, High Dependency, and Micro-Tasks.\n\nA dynamic calendar/timeline component showing scheduled \"Execution Blocks\" generated by the AI to prevent user procrastination.\n\nPlaceholder structures or mock fetch handlers representing function calls (e.g., schedule_calendar_block, parse_deadline_urgency) to simulate an autonomous agent workflow.\n\nEnsure the styling is modern, clean, and minimizes cognitive load for users who are already feeling overwhelmed."
    items {
      text: "Build a web application for an AI-powered proactive productivity companion called \"Last-Minute Life Saver.\"\n\nThe application must feature a split-screen dashboard layout optimized for desktop viewports. The left side must feature an intentional, low-friction conversational chat interface where users can type unstructured, frantic \"brain dumps\" of their schedules, tasks, or upcoming deadlines. The right side must feature a dynamic, interactive visual timeline and task execution board that updates in real-time based on the AI\'s analysis.\n\nKey components to generate in the React frontend:\n\nA clean Chat UI with state management to pass unstructured user inputs to a backend service.\n\nA Task Triage Matrix that visually categorizes tasks into structural states: Urgent & Critical, High Dependency, and Micro-Tasks.\n\nA dynamic calendar/timeline component showing scheduled \"Execution Blocks\" generated by the AI to prevent user procrastination.\n\nPlaceholder structures or mock fetch handlers representing function calls (e.g., schedule_calendar_block, parse_deadline_urgency) to simulate an autonomous agent workflow.\n\nEnsure the styling is modern, clean, and minimizes cognitive load for users who are already feeling overwhelmed."
    }
  }
}
