  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the AI Companion**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on defining \"Last-Minute Life Saver,\" this AI productivity companion. The core of its design centers around a split-screen dashboard, a chat interface on the left and a task execution board on the right. This layout aims for intuitive, real-time management.\n\n\n**Refining the Feature Set**\n\nI\'m now integrating the features. I\'m focusing on the Chat UI for processing \"brain dumps,\" the Task Triage Matrix and Execution Blocks on the calendar/timeline. I\'ve built the mock fetch handlers to simulate autonomous agent workflows. I\'m also preparing the styling with Tailwind CSS for a clean UI. I am also integrating the date-fns and uuid libraries.\n\n\n**Implementing the Backend**\n\nI\'m now focused on the backend setup, specifically an Express server with Vite integration. I\'ve outlined the `package.json` scripts and begun defining the `server.ts` file to handle API endpoints. The plan is to create a `/api/chat` endpoint, taking user input, passing it to Gemini, and rigidly structuring the response. I\'ll use structured outputs to ensure a fixed JSON response.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 838815724
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
