  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Applying Design Theme**\n\nI\'m currently working on incorporating the \"Professional Polish\" design theme into the app. This involves switching from the existing color scheme to one based on `slate`, using `blue` for primary accents, which I think will bring a much more elegant feel. I am focusing on making the color changes consistent and globally effective.\n\n\n**Implementing Color Updates**\n\nI\'ve specified `red` for urgent items and `amber` for dependencies. This also requires minor layout adjustments, like chat bubble backgrounds and input box styling. I\'ve begun reviewing the existing files, examining the current styling and preparing to adjust background and text colors. I\'m focusing on consistency in the chat interface and the matrix components.\n\n\n**Adapting Board Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m adapting the `TimelineBoard` styling to match the new aesthetic by incorporating the same colors and borders. This means using `border-slate-200`, `rounded-2xl`, and `p-6`. Furthermore, I\'ll modify the `TimelineBoard` to integrate the absolute positioning concept used in the design for execution blocks, since it\'s now a vertical list. I\'m also planning to integrate an agent status bar or processing state indicator at the bottom.\nI\'ll edit `src/App.tsx` and `src/components/ChatInterface.tsx` to accommodate the design changes.\n\n\n**Refining Text Styling**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `src/App.tsx` and updating the base styling to align with the new theme. Specifically, I\'m updating text and border colors, going from `neutral` to `slate`. For instance, I replaced `text-neutral-900` with `text-slate-900` and `border-neutral-200` with `border-slate-200`. The changes also involve revising the background to `bg-slate-50`. These edits are designed to improve visual cohesion.\n\n\n**Updating Chat Interface**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the chat interface\'s visual aspects. I\'m targeting its container styling to align with the design system. I\'m paying attention to the `border-slate-200`, the shadow effect, and the background color. Additionally, I need to adjust padding and margins to maintain visual consistency throughout the interface. I\'m updating `src/components/ChatInterface.tsx` to align with the new design.\n\n\n**Refining Layout and Components**\n\nI\'m now integrating the header and section components for the Execution Dashboard. I\'m focusing on layout adjustments and component structure within the `src/App.tsx` file. I\'m paying attention to padding, margins, and spacing, ensuring that these elements fit into the design\'s overall aesthetic and that they\'re responsive. The goal is a clean, effective visual representation.\n\n\n**Adjusting Timeline Display**\n\nI\'m now revising the TimelineBoard component, refining the display, and incorporating changes. I\'m focusing on the component\'s integration within the overall layout, ensuring that the timeline interacts smoothly with the rest of the dashboard components. I\'ve updated the `TimelineBoard` to integrate with the agent status indicator. My focus is still on ensuring that the updates align with the aesthetic and responsiveness of the design.\n\n\n**Integrating Agent Status**\n\nI\'ve integrated the agent status indicator into the timeline. I\342\200\231m now updating the display within the component, with a dynamic status bar featuring colors and text that change based on processing state. I\'m focusing on ensuring it\'s both informative and visually aligned. I\'m making sure to keep the indicator responsive.\n\n\n**Revising Chat Styling**\n\nI\'m now revising the chat styling in `src/components/ChatInterface.tsx` to align with the evolving design. I\'m updating the `bg-white`, `border-neutral-200`, `border-neutral-100`, `text-neutral-900`, `text-neutral-500`, `text-neutral-800`, and `bg-neutral-100` classes to match the updated color scheme. I\'m focusing on consistency with the newer changes I\'ve made across other components and elements of the app.\n\n\n**Refining Indicator Styling**\n\nI\'m now refining the agent status indicator, focusing on the styles applied to the loader and processing state text. Specifically, I am going to update the colors within the `isProcessing` conditional to the updated design, and to ensure that the styling of the indicator is consistent with the current theme. I am considering slight adjustments to the animation timing to enhance the visual feedback and reduce visual overload.\n\n\n**Evaluating Input Field**\n\nI\'m now concentrating on the text input field within the chat interface, and I\342\200\231m assessing its existing styling, particularly in `ChatInterface.tsx`. I\342\200\231m focused on updating the background and border classes. I\'m also considering adjustments to padding and margins. I\'m aiming for an enhanced visual appeal.\n\n\n**Assessing Chat Display**\n\nI\'m now focused on the chat display\'s rendering of messages, targeting visual enhancements. I\'m reviewing the message layout, paying attention to the alignment and formatting within the chat bubbles to ensure they are consistent and readable, especially concerning the styling, colors, and shadows. I\'m also ensuring the message display integrates seamlessly with any ongoing processing indicators, making them visually distinct yet unobtrusive. I am evaluating the system message display, and the rendering of user and assistant messages to improve distinction.\n\n\n**Updating Message Styling**\n\nI\'m now revising the styling of the message bubbles. I\'m updating their backgrounds, borders, and shadows to ensure they align perfectly with the overall theme. I am focusing on the visual hierarchy to make the differentiation between user and assistant messages clear, while maintaining a clean and modern look. I am also making sure the chat bubbles are readable, and not intrusive.\n\n\n**Evaluating Input Field**\n\nI\'m now focusing on assessing the text input field\'s styling, specifically in `ChatInterface.tsx`. I\'m updating background, border, padding, and margin classes for a consistent design. I\'m aiming for enhanced visual appeal and readability, ensuring a seamless fit with the updated theme.\n\n\n**Refining List Component**\n\nI\'m now revising a list component within the application to match the evolving design standards. I am refining the styling and layout for enhanced visual appeal and readability, ensuring a seamless fit with the updated theme. I am paying particular attention to the use of shadows, background colors, and borders to create a clean, consistent look. I\'m focusing on ensuring its seamless integration with the existing components.\n\n\n**Refining Board Display**\n\nI\'m now integrating new list component into the display. I\'m focusing on layout adjustments and component structure to achieve integration within existing elements. I\'m adjusting the background and text colors to the updated aesthetic, and ensuring that the list items maintain visual consistency with other elements in the timeline, with a strong focus on improved visual clarity.\n\n\n**Integrating List Display**\n\nI\'m now integrating the list components into existing areas, revising styling and refining the layout for the application. I\'m modifying colors, borders, and shadows to align with the new design theme and ensure seamless integration across the board. The goal is consistent visual clarity and an improved user experience.\n\n\n**Adjusting Task Display**\n\nI\'m now integrating new task list components into the display, focusing on their layout and structure to integrate with existing application elements. I\'m updating their background and text colors to the updated aesthetic, ensuring consistent visual clarity and a cohesive appearance throughout. I am also making sure that elements of the tasks maintain the current application\'s visual style.\n\n\n**Adapting Absolute Positioning**\n\nI\'m now adapting the timeline display to include elements that would be absolutely positioned in the provided reference. This requires re-evaluating layout strategy since time is not fixed or a specific schedule. I am focusing on making the positioning flexible, and integrated with the timeline board. This means rethinking how to position the timeline elements within the list structure I am working on. I am planning to enhance the component by integrating a `isProcessing` flag.\n\n\n**Implementing Timeline Updates**\n\nI\'m now integrating the provided code, adapting the vertical list styling to incorporate left borders and consistent colors. I\'m focusing on creating visual distinction and cohesion within the timeline components. I\'m evaluating the styling for the time blocks. I am updating my existing `TimelineBoard` to integrate with the new changes, particularly with the `bg-blue-600/10` and `border-l-4` classes.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Integration**\n\nI\'m now focusing on integrating the new timeline styling with existing elements, particularly the vertical lines and circular markers. I\'ve also incorporated new marker states such as the \'buffer\' block style and the \'break\' block. I\'m focusing on ensuring these additions integrate seamlessly, and I\'m updating the existing \'TimelineBoard\'. Specifically, I\'m integrating the updated styles for visual hierarchy.\n\n\n**Integrating Timeline Updates**\n\nI\'m now implementing the vertical list, focusing on adjusting the overall styling of the existing TimelineBoard. I\'m focusing on incorporating visual distinctions, such as left borders and background colors. I am examining the updated styles and classes in the given code snippet, particularly the use of `bg-blue-600/10` and `border-l-4`. My focus is creating a cohesive aesthetic and a visually distinct timeline.\n\n\n**Evaluating Timeline Components**\n\nI\'m now integrating the provided timeline code to apply visual distinction and a cohesive structure. I\'m focusing on adopting the vertical list styling from the code, including the incorporation of left borders and colors. I am updating my existing `TimelineBoard` component to implement the visual distinctions provided in the code. I am focusing on ensuring that the updates are seamless and cohesive within the overall design.\n\n\n**Implementing Timeline Updates**\n\nI\'m now focusing on adapting the timeline\'s visual elements using the provided code. I\'m updating my `TimelineBoard` by incorporating the vertical list styling and applying visual distinctions, particularly left borders and background colors. I\'m focusing on adopting the provided `bg-blue-600/10` and `border-l-4` classes, to ensure a cohesive look. I am paying close attention to the visual hierarchy of the timeline.\n\n\n**Refining Task Styling**\n\nI\'m now implementing the vertical list, specifically focusing on refining the styling for each task item. I am focusing on the visual hierarchy, incorporating distinctions like left borders, background colors, and circular markers, making sure that these tasks follow the current styling. I am examining the updated styles and classes in the given code, particularly the use of `bg-blue-600/10` and `border-l-4`.\n\n\n**Refining Task Display**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the styling for each task item within the timeline, incorporating visual distinctions. I\'m prioritizing visual hierarchy with left borders, background colors, and circular markers, to ensure they match the current styling of the timeline. Specifically, I\'m examining the `bg-blue-600/10` and `border-l-4` classes from the code snippet to ensure the visual clarity.\n\n\n"
